# <a name="translating"></a> Translating Texts
To translate text using the Microsoft Azure Text Analytics API, the text to be translated and the language of the text need to be specified.

The following code snippet shows an example of how to create a translation request using the `Translate` method.

```csharp
var text = "Hello, world!";
var targetLanguage = "es";

var translateRequest = new TranslateRequest
{
    Text = text,
    TargetLanguage = targetLanguage
};

var translateResponse = await translateClient.TranslateAsync(translateRequest);
var translations = translateResponse.Documents.Translations;
```

The output of the `Translate` method is a list of `Translation` objects, which represent the translated text for each language specified in the request.

## <a name="translating-with-language-detection"></a> Translating with Language Detection
If you don't know the language of the text, you can use the `DetectLanguage` method to automatically detect the language of the input text.

The `DetectLanguage` method returns a list of language detection options, along with the language that was detected.

```csharp
var text = "Hello, world!";
var translateResponse = await client.DetectLanguageAsync(new DetectLanguageInput { Text = text });
var language = translateResponse.Documents[0].Language;
```

You can then use the detected language as the target language for the translation request.

```csharp
var targetLanguage = "es";

var translateRequest = new TranslateRequest
{
    Text = text,
    TargetLanguage = targetLanguage
};
```
